-- Banco do Brasil May Boost Loans 20% in 2012, Bendine Tells Globo
-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 2012-06-24T17:07:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-24/banco-do-brasil-may-boost-loans-20-in-2012-bendine-tells-globo.html
Banco do Brasil SA  sees lending
expanding almost 20 percent this year after the bank cut
 interest rates  it charges to customers, Chief Executive Officer
Aldemir Bendine told  O Globo .  Banco do Brasil is in talks with the Ermirio de Moraes
family to invest in Banco Votorantim after higher bad-loan
provisions by the lender, the Rio de Janeiro-based newspaper
said, citing Bendine. He declined to say how much the bank will
invest in Votorantim.  The Ermirio de Moraes family and Banco do Brasil share
control of Votorantim, with about 50 percent each.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in  Sao Paulo  at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net . 